author: ETA PRIME
description:
Lenovo’s new LOQ (pronounced Lock) Gaming Desktop might be the most surprising prebuilt PC I’ve tested in a long time. Lenovo dropped a compact, super-clean small form factor gaming tower—but the twist?
They paired an RTX 3060 Ti with a Ryzen 7 8745HS mobile CPU… and the performance is WAY better than I expected.
In this video, I fully break down the design, specs, thermals, benchmarks, and real-world gaming performance at 1080p, 1440p, and even 4K.
If you’re looking for a new gaming PC that stays budget-friendly without feeling “cheap,” the LOQ Tower might shock you too.
